I bought these earrings because I needed something easy to put in, and that needs no backing to stay in.

These 13mm just go in easy and don't require backings, even though they include them if you think you need them. I didn't.

When I put them in you can see in my picture that the bottoms don't extend very far below my earlobe. I pinched the bottoms a bit to be sure they would not come out as I cannot handle backings.

title: Understated and elegant.
text:
What do I know from women's earrings? Fortunately, the pictures and description are accurate and you can decide if the intended recipient will wear them with delight or return them for something else that you couldn't believe anyone would wear. Anyway, that's been my life experience when buying jewelry for my wife.

That said, I think these are attractive. They're sterling silver and have a nice sparkle when the light hits them. They have a thick end tapering to a thin end. The thin end is not sharp and the finish is excellent. It should be noted that sterling silver is not "springy" and you can easily bend these. Fortunately, you can also bend them back, if necessary. From an aesthetic view, these earrings provide a similar amount of overall "sparkle" as a small diamond stud at a much lower price. They are very light, certainly lighter that hoop earrings.

Sterling silver will tarnish and you will need to clean them with a mild silver polish from time to time to restore the sparkle.

Also be sure that the person who is to wear them is not allergic to silver. Some people can only wear earrings with gold or stainless steel posts.

title: Great Part Replacement - Should have been designed like this by Lazy Boy
text:
We have 4 Lazy Boy power recliners. We like them very much. However one has broken twice for the same reason. We had a repairman in to fix it the first time, $200. He put in the correct Lazy Boy parts. The same part broke again. Clearly poorly designed.

This kit addresses the problem. It replaces a plastic part that is not up to the task. The metal part provided in the kit should last the lifetime of the chair. If this breaks on the other recliners I will buy this kit again.

Note, this is a straightforward repair BUT there are a lot of pieces and parts. I have an extensive background in auto mechanics, carpentry, some cabinet making, and model aircraft, so I am used to taking things apart and putting them together while I figure things out. If you don't have some mechanical background, don't attempt this. You are removing two parts and replacing them with one part that looks completely different. You are adding spacers to account for this and it can be a bit confusing what goes where.

The order of disassembly and assembly are clearly outlined in the instructions and there are small pictures provided that help, but not all of the parts in the pictures are labeled with names that I could correlate to the part. So I had to figure out what he was talking about.

The big metal part, the main part, can go on the drive rod 8 different ways. I put it on wrong twice and had to take it all apart. Got it right on the third try. Not the fault of the manufacturer as much as it can be easy to miss interpret what is being said and what is being shown in the instructions.

What really helped is that I took extensive digital photos with my phone before and during the disassembly. I referred to these extensively as I put things back together. This made a HUGE difference. Take LOTS of photos from various angles so you can confirm how things go back together.

Overall I am very pleased with the replacement part and the kit. It had everything I needed to do the repair.

Note that in several places he calls for applying lithium grease to the bearings. This is not provided but is readily available in small tubes from Home Depot, Lowes, most hardware or automotive supply stores. Don't skip this or things will wear out quickly.

Hopefully, I won't need another one but if I do, the repair will go much more quickly. I am really happy this parts kit was available through Amazon or I would never have found it. At best I would have bought the same Lazy Boy part that would surly have broken again.

text: I'm pretty much satisfied with this art because it is so neatly done. The white wood makes it a little nursery ish which would be delightful for many, however, I was aiming for a 13 year old boy so I may have missed the mark with all the bright white and may have to rework after the holidays. Overall, I wish the wolf was a solid black and the mountains were a little more organic. I like the watercolor effect in the sky and plenty going on in the scene. To the artist, we just moved 800 miles and the boys are not asking for anything for their rooms and sitting shoulder to shoulder at the computer or walking the shops they haven't chosen anything. I appreciate being able to customize our new home with this original mixed media hand art. Thank you!

title: So this is what Yen smells like
text:
As a huge fan of the Witcher books and video games, I had to order this. Every time the reference to "Lilac and Gooseberries" came up I found myself wondering, "what on earth does Lilac and Gooseberries smell like?"

Well.

It smells like the perfect summer day when everything in your world is perfect. When the sun is warm but not too hot, you've been outside all day, and now you're relaxing in the grass with someone who loves you and who you are safe with. No wonder Geralt chases Yen over Triss (#teamtriss). Yen just smells good.

The first thing that hits you is the flowery scent of the lilac. It's strong, but not overwhelming and doesn't make your nose burn or your throat scratch like so many flowery perfumes. It's just like smelling an actual lilac. Then the gooseberry scent comes through. Juicy, fruity, almost mouthwatering. I didn't know it was possible to smell this good.

My cat hates when I wear scented lotions. He'll run from me and wrinkle his nose up. When I wear the perfume, hand cream, or lotion he'll come over to me and stick his little freckled nose against my skin and sniff me. I also keep catching him going after the box that I keep these in.

I haven't burnt the candle or even opened the lip balm yet, but I make candles myself and the quality of this candle is good. I can't wait to try it. I think it will have a pretty good scent throw.

I was a little hesitant to order because of the price, not that I thought it was overpriced (I'm willing to pay small businesses for their time and efforts) but because I just wasn't sure if it was worth spending this much money on "fancy" beauty items. I'm not a glamorous lady. But it was so worth every penny and when I've used these up I will order more.

They also came extremely well packaged. It showed up in my metal mailbox on a very hot day and the hand cream had a little bit of oil seeping out of the container but that does not surprise me at all and I was honestly impressed because when I opened it it didn't look melted or separated at all (and it had to be well over 100 F in that mailbox). Every item was wrapped in bubble wrap and then wrapped again in paper.
